1157,IssuesEvent,2017-01-16 12:47:02+00:00,6865808,danilop/yas3fs,7735945,ollietreend,,,opened,New AWS region: eu-west-2,[],[],0,"Hi,

I'm trying to use `yas3fs` with the new AWS region `eu-west-2`.

Unfortunately `yas3fs` fails to start, with the error message:

```
ERROR wrong AWS region 'eu-west-2' for S3, use -h for help.
```

It looks like this is caused due to the new region not existing in `boto.s3.regions()`'s list of regions. From [\_\_init\_\_.py lines 848-849](https://github.com/danilop/yas3fs/blob/774426041850155185ce64fb1746a3daedf61230/yas3fs/__init__.py#L848-L849):

```python
if not self.aws_region in (r.name for r in boto.s3.regions()):
    error_and_exit(""wrong AWS region '%s' for S3"" % self.aws_region)
```

I'm not a python guy, but it looks as if `boto` has been deprecated in favour of [`boto3`](https://github.com/boto/boto3). Is there anything we can do to add support for those new regions into `yas3fs`?",{},{}
