<type 'exceptions.OSError'>: Too many open files
The command was:

	bedtools sort -i stdin

Things to check:

	* Too many files open -- please submit a bug report so that this can be fixed
```
I'm trying to merge transcripts and CDS intervals per gene and I keep running into this bug. My test list is only 103 genes, but my full list will be >1000. I'm using the interval function rather than actually writing to files, but I still get this bug. Here is some example code:

```python
def make_intervals(loc_list):
    for data in loc_list:
        seqid=data.split(':')[0]
        loc_str = data.split(':')[1]
        start=str(int(loc_str.split('-')[0])-1)
        stop=loc_str.split('-')[1]
        yield pybedtools.create_interval_from_list([seqid, start, stop])

def mergeBed(bed):
    sorted_bed = bed.sort()
    bed_merge = sorted_bed.merge()
    tot_len = 0
    for feature in bed_merge:
        feat_len = feature.stop - feature.start
        tot_len += feat_len
    return tot_len

for gene in geneIdsToGet:
    pybedtools.cleanup(remove_all=True)
    for tx in gene2tx[gene]:
            #get exon info first
             for exon in tx2exon[tx]:
                tot_ex_list.append(exon)  
     if len(tot_ex_list)>0:
         exon_bed = pybedtools.BedTool(make_intervals(tot_ex_list))
         ex_len = mergeBed(exon_bed)
````",{},{}
