Apr 06 08:43:38 host bash[20676]: DEBUG:kafka.consumer.fetcher:Adding fetch request for partition TopicPartition(topic='click', partition=8) at offset 82312```

These messages are not then produced from the high level API.  A stripped down example of the code we're using.

```
self.consumer = KafkaConsumer(bootstrap_servers=self.kafka_hosts,
                              group_id=self.group_id,
                              auto_offset_reset='earliest',
                              heartbeat_interval_ms=1000)

### Lots of code missing.###

with open(file_path, 'a') as fp:

    for msg in self.consumer:

        # Transform (this decodes some json and pops some fields).
        fp.write(transform(msg.value))
        line_total += 1

        # Check if we're hitting our target.
        # We implement a batch pull timeout due to low activity at times.
        if line_total == self.line_target or self._max_fetch_time():

            # Force consumer commit.
            self.consumer.commit()

            break
```

I've had a look through the library and the message path seems quite simple, the only point I can see where we may be losing messages is https://github.com/dpkp/kafka-python/blob/master/kafka/consumer/fetcher.py#L422.  We're not however calling seek() manually anywhere?  I think it would be good to change this to log something when continue is called as currently that could be a bit of a black hole.

Any pointers on where to go from here would be good.  We're seeing around a 5% discrepancy on ~25k messages a day which is quite considerable.",{},{}
