3174,IssuesEvent,2016-12-06 14:04:14+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,74234,adriannye,,,opened,support for pyplot eps images,[],[],0,"
Powerpoint accepts EPS images and there are existing libraries for creating EPS barcharts and piecharts that are way more flexible than the ones in pptx, such as pyplot.    It would be better to focus on developing the powerpoint specific features, instead of reinventing a complete plotting library.  First step would be to document how to use pyplot to create an image and use it in a powerpoint.",{},{}
3176,IssuesEvent,2018-07-24 21:34:12+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,22569257,drkpasngr,,,opened,Help removing leading blank line before paragraph.runs text within table cells,[],[],0,"I have some code that outputs the below table.

