3203,IssuesEvent,2015-09-12 11:01:35+00:00,33454782,tkem/mopidy-dleyna,2833077,tkem,,,opened,Server lost permanently,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/tkem/mopidy-dleyna/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}]",[],0,"Sometimes, usually after a couple of days running without problems, DLNA media servers get ""lost"" and will not be found again, even after library refresh.

This could be due to local network problems or dLeyna/Mopidy/Mopidy-dLeyna signal/notification issues. Until this is analyzed in more detail, a library refresh should also actively refresh the known servers and not depend on found/lost signals.

",{},{}
3206,IssuesEvent,2015-10-10 15:43:56+00:00,28882767,tkem/mopidy-mobile,2833077,tkem,,,closed,Use angular events,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/tkem/mopidy-mobile/labels/refactoring', 'name': 'refactoring', 'color': '207de5'}]",[],3,"Mopidy events should be `$broadcast`ed on the `$rootScope`. Mopidy's `event` object can be passes as `args`. Event names should be prefixed with `mopidy:`.
This allows to remove all the `$destroy` deregistration stuff, and reduce complexity in `connection`. Future event arguments (`tracklist.getOptions()`) can be shimmed. The mopidy instance could be passed as an additional argument, if still needed. Not sure what to do with the connection `online` and `offline` events, as for now.",{},{}
