3259,IssuesEvent,2017-11-09 16:48:12+00:00,8292338,ultrabug/py3status,13064767,Artlant,,,opened,add deadbeef мodule Format placeholders {file_name},[],[],0,"Hi!
Sometimes it happens that the file has no `title / artist` tags and then it makes sense to print out the file name. This is for example when downloading the `.m4a` file from _youtube_.
 for the `deadbeef` command looks like this. 
`deadbeef --nowplaying ""%f""`

Just maybe it makes sense also to cut out the file extension and leaving only the name.
`deadbeef --nowplaying ""%f""` | regex (.\w{2,4}$)

But it's convenient to design a kind
`format = '[{output} == null ] | {file_name}'`
",{},{}
