3452,IssuesEvent,2016-10-18 15:52:29+00:00,41542522,cztomczak/cefpython,1187415,cztomczak,,,reopened,Refactor GTK example to use PyGObject instead of PyGTK (still Open because of possible issue with mixed GTK 2 and GTK 3 symbols),[],[],2,"I've tried installing PyGTK for Python 3 (with pyenv) and I'm having a hard time. Looks like PyGTK is deprecated according to this blog post: [End of an Era: PyGTK](http://johnstowers.co.nz/2011/04/03/end-of-an-era-pygtk/). The alternative is to use [PyGObject](https://wiki.gnome.org/Projects/PyGObject). 

Here are some examples:
* [gtk-demo.py](https://git.gnome.org/browse/pygobject/tree/demos/gtk-demo/gtk-demo.py)
* [cairo-demo.py](https://git.gnome.org/browse/pygobject/tree/examples/cairo-demo.py)
* [signal.py](https://git.gnome.org/browse/pygobject/tree/examples/signal.py)

Related issues: 
* #207 - examples/ root dir
* #246 - gtk example should use MessageLoop().

See also the Refactor Examples project.

",{},{}
3454,IssuesEvent,2017-10-28 05:34:50+00:00,41542522,cztomczak/cefpython,1187415,cztomczak,,,opened,Update to Chromium v62,"[{'id': 473567830, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/cztomczak/cefpython/labels/next%20release', 'name': 'next release', 'color': 'bfe5bf', 'default': False}]",[],0,"Chromium v62 is currently a [supported Release branch](https://bitbucket.org/chromiumembedded/cef/wiki/BranchesAndBuilding#markdown-header-current-release-branches-supported
) in upstream CEF and can be downloaded from [Spotify builds](http://opensource.spotify.com/cefbuilds/index.html).

Notable changes since v57 (incomplete list):
- Ubuntu 12 / 13 and Debian 7 no more supported by upstream Chromium/CEF (Issue #401)
- There is a breaking change in v59 in offscreen windows, they are now automatically transparent due to this [CEF commit](https://bitbucket.org/chromiumembedded/cef/commits/3f71138d64586d774f645a6db5283b5205ea9df4). To make a offscreen window non-transparent you need to set the background colour using `BrowserSettings.background_color`. Ref: https://github.com/cefsharp/CefSharp/pull/2114

New branch ""cefpython58"" should be created from current master before updating.",{},{}
