5181,IssuesEvent,2016-02-02 20:19:22+00:00,27406686,markfinger/python-react,12259799,BenAtEventbrite,,,opened,Issue with _PROXY_DJANGO_SETTINGS?,[],[],0,"The [docs](https://github.com/markfinger/python-react#settings) say that I can add settings for `RENDER` & `RENDER_URL`, but it's not working. I've traced it down to [`conf.py`](https://github.com/markfinger/python-react/blob/master/react/conf.py#L9) and the `_PROXY_DJANGO_SETTINGS` private variable.

It's initialized to `False`, but there's no way to to set it `True`. So in [`RENDER_URL`](https://github.com/markfinger/python-react/blob/master/react/conf.py#L13-L14) & [`RENDER`](https://github.com/markfinger/python-react/blob/master/react/conf.py#L25-L26) it always returns the default settings `_render_url` & `_render`.

My current workaround is to call [`configure`](https://github.com/markfinger/python-react/blob/master/react/conf.py#L35-L39) directly so that I can override the defaults:

```python
from react import conf
from django.conf import settings
conf.settings.configure(settings.REACT.get('RENDER_URL'), settings.REACT.get('RENDER'))
```

...but this seems wrong. Am I missing something?

Thanks for the library BTW! ",{},{}
