6249,IssuesEvent,2017-10-29 16:36:08+00:00,2381550,astrofrog/mpl-scatter-density,314716,astrofrog,,,closed,Make it possible to specify a color for each marker based on a third value,"[{'id': 650792047, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/astrofrog/mpl-scatter-density/labels/enhancements', 'name': 'enhancements', 'color': 'c2e0c6', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Matplotlib's scatter method allows one to pass a ``c=`` argument which takes an array of values that is then mapped to color via a colormap. We could so something similar here. I think this could be done as follows:

* Implement support for weights in fast-histogram
* Call the histogram with ``c`` as the weights
* Map the result with the specified colormap

This is an approximation - in practice there's no reason that the average color in a pixel would be the color of the average, but the above is by far the fastest way to do this.",{},{}
