6426,IssuesEvent,2017-01-01 21:59:58+00:00,26947860,facelessuser/pymdown-extensions,1055125,facelessuser,,,closed,Deprecate pymdownx.pymdown wrapper extension,"[{'id': 151758139, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/facelessuser/pymdown-extensions/labels/Maintenance', 'name': 'Maintenance', 'color': '207de5', 'default': False}]",[],1,"I originally added the pymdown extension (which includes the main extensions with most common settings) as a way to easily include most of the extensions in this module.  I don't even ever use it.  I don't think most other people would either.  I personally configure each one I want individually.  The github extension at least makes sense as you are emulating a Markdown subset, but pymdown just seems like more work to maintain.  I'd like to deprecate it and remove it.  Let people individually include what they want as I imagine that is actually how people do use it.",{},{}
