7070,IssuesEvent,2017-12-15 23:35:04+00:00,56217288,confluentinc/confluent-kafka-python,2366527,rmechler,9439498,confluentinc,opened,How to consume tombstone messages with Consumer.poll()?,[],[],0,"Description
===========
Consumer.poll() does not seem to return messages that have a key but no value. My application needs to know when a value is deleted. How can I make poll() return these messages, is there configuration I can set?

How to reproduce
================
Use Producer.produce() to send a message that has a key but no value (for a compacted topic). Try to Consume using Consumer.poll().

Checklist
=========
Please provide the following information:

 - [ ] confluent-kafka-python and librdkafka version (`confluent_kafka.version()` and `confluent_kafka.libversion()`): 0.11.0, 0.11.1~1confluent4.0.0-1
 - [ ] Apache Kafka broker version: 0.11.0
 - [ ] Client configuration: `{
    'bootstrap.servers': BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS,
    'group.id': GROUP_ID,
    'security.protocol': 'ssl',
    'ssl.ca.location': 'ssl/kafka-ca.crt',
    'ssl.certificate.location': 'ssl/kafka-client.crt',
    'ssl.key.location': 'ssl/kafka-client.key',
    'default.topic.config': {
        'auto.offset.reset': 'earliest'
    }
}`
 - [ ] Operating system: Debian 8


",{},{}
