7079,IssuesEvent,2018-07-20 14:48:32+00:00,14991049,nccgroup/Scout2,4206926,j4v,4067082,nccgroup,closed,Scout2 does not detect credentials when running on Amazon ECS,"[{'id': 69447324, 'node_id': 'MDU6TGFiZWw2OTQ0NzMyNA==', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nccgroup/Scout2/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'j4v', 'id': 4206926, 'node_id': 'MDQ6VXNlcjQyMDY5MjY=', 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars3.githubusercontent.com/u/4206926?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/j4v', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j4v/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",3,"When running Scout2 on ECS it appears to not be able to retrieve the instance credentials provided by the IAM role for the task.

When running Scout2 with no arguments it returns:
Error: could not find AWS credentials. Use the --help option for more information.

I suspect that this is due to an updated metadata URL specific to container instances. 

EC2 metadata:
http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/

ECS metadata:
curl 169.254.170.2$AWS_CONTAINER_CREDENTIALS_RELATIVE_URI
where an example of  $AWS_CONTAINER_CREDENTIALS_RELATIVE_URI=/v2/credentials/9f426f92-8cb7-49fe-9353-3284d427a46f

More information about IAM roles with ECS tasks can be found here:
https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECS/latest/developerguide/task-iam-roles.html

",{},{}
