7659,IssuesEvent,2016-02-29 00:45:30+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,36873,davidcelis,6117407,deis,opened,"App process died at one point, now can be listed as running but doesn't produce output",[],[],0,"I have a Twitter bot I use as a test app on my deis cluster. Recently, I noticed that it hadn't tweeted anything for a while, and when I checked on its processes it was listed as `destroyed`. I scaled back up to 1, and noticed that the process was now listed as running but doesn't produce any log output. The app has been in this state for several days and, though listed as ""running"", isn't doing anything.

I tried destroying the app and re-creating it with the same configuration and name, but when I started up the new app and checked `deis logs`, I was simply presented with the logs for my _old_ application and no new STDOUT output. I also tried editing the Procfile to change the name of my process from `cmd` to `bot`, but that still doesn't cause the app to actually come up.

If I SSH into my cluster using `deisctl ssh router`, I can run `fleetctl list-units` and I _do_ see the container for my app running (it's the first one):

```
core@deis-1 ~ $ fleetctl list-units
UNIT				MACHINE				ACTIVE	SUB
