7674,IssuesEvent,2015-04-19 15:29:24+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,7757,bastilian,6117407,deis,opened,deisctl install platform hangs when < 3 nodes,[],[],0,"When running less then 3 nodes `deisctl install platform` will hang indefinitely waiting for routers to be loaded.

This is likely caused by `deisctl` itself, due to it trying to install 3 routers ([cmd.go#L441](https://github.com/deis/deis/blob/master/deisctl/cmd/cmd.go#L441)): 

```go
b.Create([]string{""router@1"", ""router@2"", ""router@3""}, wg, outchan, errchan)
```

The documentation ""strongly recommends"" 3 nodes, the above kinda ""requires"" it.

I'm not sure if simply reducing the array to just router@1 would be the right thing to do or changing the documentation to state that 3 nodes are required for deis to run correctly.",{},{}
