8156,IssuesEvent,2017-11-30 14:54:37+00:00,37137879,QCoDeS/Qcodes,23165537,WilliamHPNielsen,20478252,QCoDeS,closed,Developer pyenv installation instructions - missing requirement,[],[],0,"### Steps to reproduce
Follow steps in Developer-pyenv section of README [here](https://github.com/QCoDeS/Qcodes/blob/master/README.rst#developer-pyenv), using conda instead of pyenv (because Windows):
1. git clone https://github.com/QCoDeS/Qcodes.git $QCODES_INSTALL_DIR
2. cd $QCODES_INSTALL_DIR
3. conda create -n qcodes-dev python=3.5.2
4. activate qcodes-dev
5.  pip install -r requirements.txt
6. pip install coverage pytest-cov pytest --upgrade
7. pip install -e .
8. py.test --cov=qcodes --cov-config=.coveragerc

### Expected behaviour
Successful tests.

### Actual behaviour
Several tests failing with:  `ImportError: No module named 'hypothesis'`

### Suggested fix
replace `pip install coverage pytest-cov pytest --upgrade ` with `pip install coverage pytest-cov pytest hypothesis --upgrade` in README.rst

### System
Windows 10

master

4c7ed38f689a3e474fd454dd341c7d119be9a5ad
",{},{}
