8232,IssuesEvent,2017-04-04 18:58:12+00:00,53549881,anymail/django-anymail,639984,medmunds,17517617,anymail,closed,Email parser error message improvement,"[{'id': 339136475, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/anymail/django-anymail/labels/feature/enhancement', 'name': 'feature/enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': False}]",[],1,"We came across some issues when getting Anymail set up with our project. Ended up figuring out that the issue was that we were setting `message.reply_to` to a string instead of a `list`.

Could be a minor improvement to either (1) automatically check if that variable is set to a string and automatically put it as a single-element list, or (2) throw a more helpful error message when any variable that should be a list of email addresses like `to, bcc, cc, reply_to` is the incorrect data type.

You can reproduce this by trying to send an email where `message.reply_to = ""test@example.com""` instead of `message.reply_to = [""test@example.com""]`.

Minor little thing, but could prevent some issues in the future, since the resulting error message is pretty cryptic.

I realize this issue is pretty devoid of any specifics, so feel free to let me know if any more details would help.",{},{}
8240,IssuesEvent,2018-05-15 10:04:29+00:00,101282151,bbc/nmos-common,193922,j616,828722,bbc,closed,Negative timestamps/offsets sometimes returned as positive in strings,"[{'id': 675569007, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/bbc/nmos-common/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'j616', 'id': 193922, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/193922?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/j616', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/j616/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"The various to string routines (inc to_sec_nsec and to_sec_frac) use `self.sign * self.sec` for returning the second component when `self.sec` is 0, this will always return 0. Any timestamp/timeoffset between -0:MAX_NANOSEC and -0:1 will return their absolute equivalent.",{},{}
