9358,IssuesEvent,2018-01-03 10:34:30+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,335567,Carreau,7388996,jupyter,closed,isolated HTML rendering,[],[],2,"I am trying to render arbitrary HTML inside a notebook. 
For example, the following HTML has a DOMContentLoaded event listener:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang=""en"">
<head>
  <title>NGL - embedded</title>
  <meta charset=""utf-8"">
  <meta name=""viewport"" content=""width=device-width, user-scalable=no, minimum-scale=1.0, maximum-scale=1.0"">
</head>
<body>
  <script src=""https://cdn.rawgit.com/arose/ngl/v0.10.3/dist/ngl.js""></script>
  <script>
    var stage;
    document.addEventListener(""DOMContentLoaded"", function () {
      stage = new NGL.Stage(""viewport"");
      stage.loadFile(""rcsb://1crn.mmtf"", {defaultRepresentation: true});
    });
  </script>
  <div id=""viewport"" style=""width:800px; height:800px;""> </div>
</body>
</html>
```
Rendering with %%html fails, because it needs to be in an iframe. I know the notebook supports this via the ""isolated"" metadata parameter, but I didn't manage to make it work like that (the parameter gets overwritten).

Right now, I am using the following workaround:

```python
html = """"""
