9841,IssuesEvent,2018-01-20 06:51:57+00:00,70530854,awslabs/serverless-application-model,32497805,jfuss,3299148,awslabs,closed,Support for resources dependent on stages created by SAM,"[{'id': 797198214, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/serverless-application-model/labels/area/cloudformation', 'name': 'area/cloudformation', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}, {'id': 797198209, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/serverless-application-model/labels/area/docs', 'name': 'area/docs', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}, {'id': 797198219, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/serverless-application-model/labels/type/documentation', 'name': 'type/documentation', 'color': '0e8a16', 'default': False}, {'id': 797198212, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/awslabs/serverless-application-model/labels/type/question', 'name': 'type/question', 'color': 'd93f0b', 'default': False}]",[],2,"When using CloudFormation resources that depend on a stage being deployed (such as ApiKey and UsagePlan), it seems that the only way to fill in the stage resource value of the DependsOn attribute is to launch the CF template without any of the dependent resources and get the logical ID from the deployed Resources tab (if deploying from the console). I don't see any documentation for the logical ID naming convention of stages deployed through SAM, which is why I ran the template first to find it.

Could there be some documentation on the naming convention or a way to explicitly define/export the logical ID of stages in a SAM template so that dependent resources can use them?",{},{}
9843,IssuesEvent,2017-03-17 03:26:16+00:00,70530854,awslabs/serverless-application-model,706782,rowanu,3299148,awslabs,opened,Confusing Error message for defining S3 event,[],[],0,"Was getting this error message on a `deploy` command:

```
Failed to create the changeset: Waiter ChangeSetCreateComplete failed: Waiter encountered a terminal failure state Status: FAILED. Reason: Transform AWS::Serverless-2016-10-31 failed with: Invalid Serverless Application Specification document. Number of errors found: 1. Resource with id [ResourceFile] is invalid. property Event not defined for resource of type S3
```

The text makes it sound like I'm missing the `Event` property, but the property I was missing was `Events`. Changing my incorrect property name made the error go away.",{},{}
