10244,IssuesEvent,2017-02-08 18:23:19+00:00,51040886,Azure/azure-cli,116461,lostintangent,6844498,Azure,opened,[VM] Allow specifying additional ports to expose when creating a VM,[],[],0,"Thanks to #1982, the `az vm open-port` command provides a simple solution for managing a VM's open ports, however, it would be nice if this could also be achieved as part of the `az vm create` command, by adding a new flag that accepts a list of ports to open on the underlying NSG.

This command already allows automatically exposing the right port for SSH/RDP access, and it would be a nice addition to also open more ports in a declarative way, without needing to use an additional command (either `vm open-port` or `network nsg rule create`) in order to satisfy simple scenarios (e.g. spinning up a web server VM that will always need port 80 exposed).

```shell
az vm create -n <name> -g <group> --image UbuntuLTS --expose-ports 80
```",{},{}
