10488,IssuesEvent,2017-01-31 04:28:34+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,closed,Old pex version installed when running pants bootstrap script,"[{'id': 22426646, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 137550486, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/in-progress', 'name': 'in-progress', 'color': '009800', 'default': False}, {'id': 234031381, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pantsbuild/pants/labels/user%20reported', 'name': 'user reported', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]","[{'login': 'jsirois', 'id': 157586, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/157586?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/jsirois', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/jsirois/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",5,"I'd send a PR, but I could not locate the source where the setup/pypi distribute code lives, so I'm shooting an issue.

I am trying to build a python distribution with `provides` and `setup_py`, but when I execute `pants` from https://pantsbuild.github.io/setup/pants, the pex version that is probably setup in `setup.py` somewhere to require `pex` in `install_requires`, is pointing the an old version (should be 1.2.1).

So I get this error:
```shell
$ ./pants setup-py src/
Exception message: Interpreter /home/klg/.cache/pants/setup/bootstrap-Linux-x86_64/pants.RenWRo/install/bin/python2.7 not capable of running Packager
```

`pex` (newest release: 1.2.1) pins setuptools to:
```python
SETUPTOOLS_REQUIREMENT = 'setuptools>=20.0,<34.0'
```

The installed version of `pants` (downloaded from https://pantsbuild.github.io/setup/pants) sets this to
```python
SETUPTOOLS_REQUIREMENT=""setuptools>=5.4.1,<31.0""
```
Which is superficial, I only note this because of my initial troubleshooting when I found https://github.com/pantsbuild/pex/blob/master/pex/installer.py#L59, which is where the above exception is raised. `self.capability` is set to `['setuptools>=2.2,<20.11']`, which now the cache/temp pants dir is installed with a newer version of setuptools (21.2.1).

When executing `pants` for the first time, the bootstrap process does `pip install pantsbuild.pants`, and pantsbuild.pants requires `pex==1.1.13` - herein lies the issue, please update the required `pex` version, if it won't break anything.

Or can someone provide a workaround.

**NOTE**: I've been able to `cd` into the temporary cache dir, activate the venv, and `pip install --upgrade pex`, but I'd rather not have to do this because my plan is to automate.

Thank you!",{},{}
10493,IssuesEvent,2016-03-22 22:10:58+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,119728,ericzundel,3065172,pantsbuild,opened,resolves are hanging: finding a stray 'pants_ivy_lock.lock' file under ~/.ivy2,[],[],0,"We have a CI working and one report of a developer laptop consistently hanging in the ivy resolve step:

