10922,IssuesEvent,2018-01-11 12:08:56+00:00,9952134,python-visualization/folium,33519926,Conengmo,9969242,python-visualization,closed,Guidance on documentation,"[{'id': 244123954, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-visualization/folium/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': 'eb6420', 'default': False}]",[],5,"There is documentation and examples in multiple places:
- There is the [docs folder](https://github.com/python-visualization/folium/tree/master/docs), which is build and shown on [github.io](http://python-visualization.github.io/folium/docs-master/index.html). It contain an installation guide, quick start examples and the API documentation. 
- Then there is the [examples](https://github.com/python-visualization/folium/tree/master/examples) folder, which is best viewed online with [Jupyter nbviewer](http://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/python-visualization/folium/tree/master/examples/). 
- And there is a [folium_contrib](https://github.com/python-visualization/folium_contrib) repository, which contains a few user contributed examples. These are also best viewed with [Jupyter nbviewer](https://nbviewer.jupyter.org/github/python-visualization/folium_contrib/tree/master/notebooks/)

@ocefpaf can you share your plan for the structure of the documentation? I can spend some time on this, but I want to do it right :)",{},{}
