10957,IssuesEvent,2017-06-22 13:58:24+00:00,32363483,python-escpos/python-escpos,4189642,patkan,16302939,python-escpos,closed,Barcode software printing,"[{'id': 188245198, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/python-escpos/python-escpos/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb', 'default': True}]",[],4,"Some printers like in #58 do not support barcode printing or only support a subset of barcodes (as the old Epson printers).

A possible enhancement would be finding a proper library for barcode-printing. ([python-barcode](https://bitbucket.org/whitie/python-barcode)?) With this barcode could be rendered in software and then printed as images.
Ideally a new capability in https://github.com/receipt-print-hq/escpos-printer-db would be used to determine whether software-rendering is needed. (See the QR-function as an example)",{},{}
11014,IssuesEvent,2017-12-11 19:41:44+00:00,25413181,marshmallow-code/apispec,1331394,p0psicles,10334301,marshmallow-code,opened,Can't use apispec tornado plugin icw complex paths,[],[],0,"I'm trying to use apispec icw the 'apispec.ext.tornado' and 'apispec.ext.marshmallow' plugins.
Only i'm getting the following error:
```
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File ""D:\JetBrains\PyCharm 2017.2.4\helpers\pydev\pydevd.py"", line 1599, in <module>
    globals = debugger.run(setup['file'], None, None, is_module)
  File ""D:\JetBrains\PyCharm 2017.2.4\helpers\pydev\pydevd.py"", line 1026, in run
    pydev_imports.execfile(file, globals, locals)  # execute the script
  File ""D:\myproj/start.py"", line 7, in <module>
    main()
  File ""D:\myproj\medusa\__main__.py"", line 2104, in main
    application.start(sys.argv[1:])
  File ""D:\myproj\medusa\__main__.py"", line 347, in start
    self.web_server = AppWebServer(self.web_options)
  File ""D:\myproj\medusa\server\core.py"", line 230, in __init__
    spec.add_path(urlspec=urlspec)
  File ""D:\Python27\lib\site-packages\apispec\core.py"", line 211, in add_path
    raise APISpecError('Path template is not specified')
apispec.exceptions.APISpecError: Path template is not specified
```

It seems to be happening because matcher._path is None.
https://github.com/marshmallow-code/apispec/blob/dev/apispec/ext/tornado.py#L95

`urlspec.matcher._path` returns None, because of this:
https://github.com/tornadoweb/tornado/blob/master/tornado/routing.py#L571

And my route looks like this:
`'/api/v2/series/(?P<series_slug>\\w+)/episode(?:(?:(?:(?:/(?P<episode_slug>[\\w-]+))|/?)(?:(?:/(?P<path_param>\\w+))|/?))|/?)/?$'`

So because the tornado plugin uses the matcher._path, it's can't translate to an OpenApi compliant path.
Is there anything I can do about it?",{},{}
11027,IssuesEvent,2015-02-06 12:28:19+00:00,14284859,marshmallow-code/marshmallow,120115,russelldavies,10334301,marshmallow-code,opened,Implicit field creation type,[],[],0,"In the [Implicit Field Creation](http://marshmallow.readthedocs.org/en/latest/quickstart.html#refactoring-implicit-field-creation) section of the docs, it states:

>Note that name will be automatically formatted as a String and created_at will be formatted as a DateTime.

However, if looking at the `fields` attribute on the instantiated object, they are all of type `fields.Field`. There doesn't seem to be any expression matching, like `email` and `e-mail` gets mapped to `fields.Email`, in the code either so I'm presuming that the statement is erroneous and should be removed.",{},{}
