11080,IssuesEvent,2015-04-12 21:00:50+00:00,19056610,SecurityInnovation/PGPy,2621594,Commod0re,320350,SecurityInnovation,opened,Refactor parsing to use memoryviews to reduce IO when slicing the incoming data,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/SecurityInnovation/PGPy/labels/enhancement', 'name': 'enhancement', 'color': '84b6eb'}]",[],0,"During the same talk that inspired #144, I also had inspiration for a way to potentially optimize packet parsing by using memoryviews to reduce overall IO. I recall that I intended to try to do this at some point during the development of 0.3.0, but it didn't happen because the idea then was to use it in a different and less useful manner.

So, as with issue #144, I am going to benchmark and profile using the same set of data generated for benchmarking/profiling that issue, but profiling the parsing instead of the serialization",{},{}
