11524,IssuesEvent,2017-01-17 01:49:24+00:00,7695747,wal-e/wal-e,7191,fdr,3310438,wal-e,closed,Problems with Frankfurt region / S3,[],[],11,"I currently can't use WAL-E with S3 and a bucket located in Frankfurt:

`The authorization mechanism you have provided is not supported. Please use AWS4-HMAC-SHA256.`

I use a simple bucket prefix in the form of s3://mybucket/test/test. I think eu-central-1 requires Signature Version 4 Authentication unlike other regions. Strangely enough, another Bucket, also placed in the Frankfurt region, with the exact same AWS credentials and permissions, works without a hitch with WAL-E. I think it might be a problem on the end of S3.
