Even if I modified the executable and changed the ""cdq"" to be ""nop"", it still stops at the same position.
No warning, and pretending to be running.

Here is the output
~~~~
>>> simgr
<SimulationManager with 3 deadended, 3 active>
>>> simgr.active
[<SimState @ 0x401171>, <SimState @ 0x401171>, <SimState @ 0x401171>]
>>> 
~~~~
And there is the code
~~~~
  1 import angr
  2 
  3 proj = angr.Project('./BinaryPwC_8cfe86c1f4f57d49f4fee3b297b3f9b8.exe')
  4 
  5 state = proj.factory.entry_state()
  6 simgr = proj.factory.simgr(state)
  7 
  8 simgr.explore(find=0x004014A5, avoid=0x00482ED2)                      
~~~~",{},{}
