11689,IssuesEvent,2015-09-04 09:37:24+00:00,2665618,inveniosoftware/invenio,633680,jalavik,1157480,inveniosoftware,closed,xvol needed in INSPIRE,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/c_WebSearch', 'name': 'c_WebSearch', 'color': 'ededed'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/in_triage', 'name': 'in_triage', 'color': 'fef2c0'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/p_major', 'name': 'p_major', 'color': 'e11d21'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/s_INSPIRE', 'name': 's_INSPIRE', 'color': '207de5'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/inveniosoftware/invenio/labels/t_enhancement', 'name': 't_enhancement', 'color': 'eb6420'}]",[],1,"Originally by *hoc* on 2012-03-12

SPIRES had an index, xvol, which takes the volume element from the standard, journal-volume-page triplet. So in a publication note such as 
Phys.Rev. D85 (2012) 045032
the xvol is ""D85""

This is especially needed for the easy search where it is currently expected (though incorrectly coded as jvol):
http://inspirehep.net/help/easy-search
",{},{}
