11997,IssuesEvent,2018-03-16 13:39:51+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,3291951,matt-gardner,5667695,allenai,closed,Fine-tuning models,"[{'id': 680972509, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/allenai/allennlp/labels/Feature%20request', 'name': 'Feature request', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 680972344, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/allenai/allennlp/labels/Hard', 'name': 'Hard', 'color': 'bfd4f2', 'default': False}, {'id': 757402569, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/allenai/allennlp/labels/P3', 'name': 'P3', 'color': '1262a8', 'default': False}]",[],2,"We don't currently have a good way to fine-tune a trained model on a new dataset.  See https://github.com/allenai/allennlp/issues/239#issuecomment-329807455 for some discussion of this, and the rest of that issue for some context.

One way to make this work is to just allow for a `model_archive` parameter instead of `model`, or allow the `model` parameter to trainer to be a string path instead of a json object, and we take the path to be a model archive.  And if we're loading an archived model, we need to treat the vocabulary creation a little differently.",{},{}
