12445,IssuesEvent,2016-12-01 19:11:56+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,closed,linger_ms = 0 not working with rdlibkafka,"[{'id': 8945343, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}, {'id': 15352879, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/documentation', 'name': 'documentation', 'color': '0b02e1', 'default': False}, {'id': 360183304, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/help%20wanted', 'name': 'help wanted', 'color': '006b75', 'default': True}, {'id': 170576876, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/librdkafka', 'name': 'librdkafka', 'color': '006b75', 'default': False}]",[],5,"Hi,
I`m using pykafka and it`s been great, but I found a tiny bug:
when using rdlibkafka, and trying to create a producer with linger_ms=0, it raises this exception:

