12449,IssuesEvent,2016-02-26 16:58:51+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,opened,Improve protocol tests,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/backlog', 'name': 'backlog', 'color': '009800'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/testing', 'name': 'testing', 'color': 'fef2c0'}]",[],0,"The protocol unit tests currently include huge [copypasted bytestrings](https://github.com/Parsely/pykafka/blob/79e8938f55484e4c892744ec203e98998c2f7f2d/tests/pykafka/test_protocol.py#L248) that are hard to make changes to or reason about. To make these tests easier to read and write, we can make a utility that can turn this

```python
""""""
00 00 00 00 00 01 00
dummytopic
00 00 00 0c
testuserdata
""""""
```

into this:

```python
bytearray(b'\x00\x00\x00\x00\x00\x01\x00\ndummytopic\x00\x00\x00\x0ctestuserdata')
```
In other words, the utility trims whitespace and converts `\b\d\d\b` to the hex equivalent. This kind of utility pays off quickly for writing tests when developing protocol drivers.
",{},{}
12452,IssuesEvent,2016-04-25 15:34:49+00:00,4978045,Parsely/pykafka,723615,emmett9001,779641,Parsely,closed,producer in a thread blocking forever,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/Parsely/pykafka/labels/question', 'name': 'question', 'color': 'cc317c'}]",[],2,"The first code sample works, but the second sample does not. Please help.
**pykafka-2.3.0**
**python2.7**

First sample:
```python
producer = KafkaClient(hosts=kafka_server).topics[topic].get_sync_producer()
print 'start testing' # printed out
producer.produce('test 1') # seen in Kafka
print 'finish testing' # printed out
```

Second sample:
```python
producer = KafkaClient(hosts=kafka_server).topics[topic].get_sync_producer()
class Test(Process):
    def __init__(self, producer):
        self.producer = producer
    def run(self):
        print 'start testing' # printed out
        self.producer.produce('test 2') # not seen in Kafka
        print 'finish testing' # never printed out
test = Test(producer)
test.start()
```",{},{}
