12990,IssuesEvent,2016-11-15 02:11:05+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,836375,rgbkrk,12401040,nteract,closed,Document Cell Focus UX Design,"[{'id': 309219250, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nteract/nteract/labels/design', 'name': 'design', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}, {'id': 451661990, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nteract/nteract/labels/feature:%20ui/ux', 'name': 'feature: ui/ux', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]",[],11,"I'd :heart: to see us write documentation for what a notebook is in user experience terms. Right now it's a bit implicit (""it's the implementation!"") -- I think we can capture different behaviors and user intents in some solid documentation/specifications. Let's tackle Cell Focus UX design first!

@captainsafia is currently solving the input focus on click in code cells problem in #1055 (our current setup is rather pesky). Hopefully we can solve all our focus problems with a clear declaration + implementation.
## Cell Focus UX

![cell focus user experience](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/836375/19669086/48b6f02c-9a11-11e6-875a-d330fdb0f900.png)

User intents, written:
### `shift enter`
- Focus on next cell (and create it if it doesn't exist)
- Scroll to next cell
- Focus Editor at top of next cell (first line) if a code cell or a markdown cell in edit mode

Note: this is the same set of changes expected with the down arrow (for focus, not execution).
### `up arrow`
- Focus on previous cell
- Scroll to previous cell
- Focus editor at bottom of previous cell (last line) if a code cell or a markdown cell in edit mode
### `down arrow`
- Focus on next cell (and create it if it doesn't exist)
- Scroll to next cell
- Focus Editor at top of next cell (first line) if a code cell or a markdown cell in edit mode
### Click editor area
- Focus clicked cell
- Don't scroll
- Don't _manually_ focus the editor, let CodeMirror do the handling
### Click display area
- Focus clicked cell
- Don't scroll
- Don't focus the editor
### Drag cell
- Focus clicked cell
- Don't scroll
- Don't focus the editor

Since I by no means think this is a decree, I've drawn my initial thoughts on cell focus UX with crayon. We should refine this as necessary and produce a document. Happy to turn this into a Sketch document when ready.

/cc @willingc and @peggyrayzis who expressed interest in this
",{},{}
13004,IssuesEvent,2018-04-13 17:00:53+00:00,37496521,nteract/nteract,836375,rgbkrk,12401040,nteract,closed,[refactor] Passthrough CodeMirror Options and Mode more directly,"[{'id': 452904396, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/nteract/nteract/labels/pkg:editor', 'name': 'pkg:editor', 'color': 'c5def5', 'default': False}]",[],2,"As I've been working with the editor component I'm noticing some bits of indirection that I think we can clean up, making it a more close match with what we use with codemirror and the notebook format. I'm going to flesh out this issue over time, so this will probably get updated as I find more.

The notebook document spec for the codemirror mode exactly matches that of [codemirror's mode object which can be a string or object](https://codemirror.net/doc/manual.html#option_mode). We do a bit of finagling to extract a string out when we could be using the overall object.

We have a lot of props that could be passed through a single codemirror options object. We do setup a lot of custom configuration which I think should be merged in with an `Object.assign` or merge. Not sure what to do here, just a bit of code smell.

We go through several layers of changing the name of the field for source. It comes as `source` from the cells, then our editor takes it as `input`, followed by finally passing it as `value` to `codemirror-react`. I think we should just call it `source` throughout. This also bears fruit in our DOM structure where our editor is in a `<div class=""input"">`.",{},{}
