13602,IssuesEvent,2017-07-07 13:38:42+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SOS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,test run mode,"[{'id': 325435542, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SOS/labels/wontfix', 'name': 'wontfix', 'color': 'ffffff', 'default': True}]",[],1,"We have two options for debugging remote tasks:

1. dryrun mode, which executes all tasks in dryrun mode, which print scripts without executing it. 
2. We have run mode with `-J1` which submit only 1 task to the server. However, after the first task fails, it will continue to submit the rest of the tasks to the server.

I am wondering if we should introduce a `test` or `test-first` mode in which only one task is executed,

1. the rest will not be submitted if the first one fails
2. the rest will all be submitted (not -J1) if the first one succeed

The problem is there is no easy way to define ""succeed"" because a task can fail at different stages. For example, a task can fail at as early as task creation stage, or as late as running for a few minutes....",{},{}
13610,IssuesEvent,2018-02-14 00:47:10+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,917985,gaow,20074389,vatlab,opened,`_output` only shared result from the last iteration,[],[],0,"I have updated [this example](https://github.com/vatlab/sos-docs/blob/master/src/examples/LP_Forward.sos) to keep up with recent syntax changes, and with [this line](https://github.com/vatlab/sos-docs/blob/master/src/examples/LP_Forward.sos#L15) I want to share all output. But judging from [this line](https://github.com/vatlab/sos-docs/blob/master/src/examples/LP_Forward.sos#L72) and also failure to execute the example, it seems the way I specify variable sharing is problematic. How can I share all output files from the first step under current syntax?",{},{}
13612,IssuesEvent,2017-09-12 20:49:53+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,9889312,BoPeng,20074389,vatlab,closed,Notebook workflow with non-ascii characters,"[{'id': 325435536, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SoS/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],0,"Right now we use `btoa` to convert workflow collected from frontend to ascii and pass it to the backend with magic `%frontend`. However, this function will fail if the workflow contains non-ascii characters. We should try to pass the workflow in another method.",{},{}
13613,IssuesEvent,2017-08-25 23:34:27+00:00,51625787,vatlab/SoS,26916551,HenryLeongStat,20074389,vatlab,opened,Writing matrix to by using feather in Julia,"[{'id': 325435536, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/vatlab/SoS/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929', 'default': True}]",[],0,"The problem here is that: When we want to transfer a `matrix`  from `Julia` to `Python`, we need to convert the `matrix` to `dataframe` first, and then save it by using `feather`.

