13664,IssuesEvent,2017-04-03 23:08:12+00:00,46374199,IntelRealSense/librealsense,1824188,melax,14095512,IntelRealSense,opened,auto exposure for zr300 fisheye stream not working ,[],[],0,"Auto exposure for the fisheye camera doesn't work if you are getting fisheye stream data the regular way.   

```
    // during setup, add fish eye streams to application:
    dev->set_option(rs::option::fisheye_color_auto_exposure, 1);
    dev->enable_stream(rs::stream::fisheye, 640, 480, rs::format::raw8, 60);
 ...
    // in main loop:
    auto data = (unsigned char*)dev->get_frame_data(rs::stream::fisheye);
```


Digging into the code, it looks like some sort of new callback api has been added, and the fish-eye auto exposure is only provided for applications that switch over from the regular librealsense api to use the new callback mechanisms.

```
    // in librealsense/src/device.cpp   around line #469:
                if (config.callbacks[streams[i]])
                {
                    ... 
                        on_before_callback(streams[i], frame_ref, archive);

    // in zr300.cpp:
    void zr300_camera::on_before_callback( ... )
    {
        if (!to_add_frames || stream != RS_STREAM_FISHEYE)
            return;

        auto_exposure->add_frame(clone_frame(frame), archive);
    }
```

| Required Info  |   |
