13727,IssuesEvent,2017-10-23 12:29:34+00:00,59868262,aws/chalice,8456082,jonasao,2232217,aws,opened,Init Authorizer with different settings based on stage,[],[],0,"Is it possible to initialize an Authorizer (CognitoUserPoolAuthorizer) with a different set of settings based on the stage the application is deployed to?

E.g. when deploying to a ""dev"" stage, the following settings will be used:
`authorizer = CognitoUserPoolAuthorizer('dev-userpool', header='Authorization', provider_arns=['arn:aws.....dev...'])`

...while deploying to a ""prod"" stage, the following settings will be used:
`authorizer = CognitoUserPoolAuthorizer('prod-userpool', header='Authorization', provider_arns=['arn:aws.....prod....'])`

I believe it is possible to do this with a batch-script which is run before calling the `chalice deploy --stage <stage>` command, but it would have been great if this is part of the chalice framework, or could become a part of it in the future.",{},{}
13728,IssuesEvent,2018-05-22 21:36:21+00:00,59868262,aws/chalice,32965360,no-response[bot],2232217,aws,closed,Working with Swagger ?,"[{'id': 403474419, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/aws/chalice/labels/closing-soon-if-no-response', 'name': 'closing-soon-if-no-response', 'color': '5319e7', 'default': False}]",[],1,"Apologies but I am having trouble finding this in the docs; but what are the recommended ways of working with Swagger and Chalice ? I have a team of devs building stateless Chalice POST apps/APIs - JSON in, JSON out - and need a sensible documentation solution. I mention Swagger because it seems to be what everybody uses. Ideally I would like devs to write simple docs as part of their Chalice projects (maybe in YAML form ? maybe annotated source code ?), have them deployed to AWS via Chalice and then have a nice set of generated HTML docs available at the Chalice endpoint. Does anything nice and simple like this exist ? Assuming Chalice supports Swagger could someone point me to the docs and maybe describe the workflow in very simple terms ? Asking because Swagger seems like a beast with multiple different products and its very hard to know where to start. Thanks in advance :-)",{},{}
