13836,IssuesEvent,2016-02-18 20:05:02+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,2184487,JDWarner,897180,scikit-image,opened,Add Issue templates and declutter root directory,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/scikit-image/scikit-image/labels/easy', 'name': 'easy', 'color': 'fc9a91'}]",[],0,"GitHub now supports a `.github/` directory for their new Issue/PR templates. There are common enough things we should know in essentially all Issues we should probably enable the Issue template requesting Python version, scikit-image version, and ensure full tracebacks are included if available.

We should also move `CONTRIBUTING.txt` into that directory, decluttering the root. It's always been less than ideal having `CONTRIBUTORS.txt` and `CONTRIBUTING.txt` right next to each other.

These are easy, quality-of-life changes which do not need to go in before 0.12.",{},{}
