14104,IssuesEvent,2017-03-20 16:14:02+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,391586,pvanderlinden,6392739,conda,opened,Switching python 3.6 -> 3.5 with conda env breaks conda,[],[],0,"Easiest to reproduce this, is to use the latest miniconda3 docker image, and then make an environment.yml file with the following contents:
```
name: root
dependencies:
- python=3.5
- pip:
  - bson
```
When running `conda env update` you will get the following error:
```
Unable to install package for pip.

Please double check and ensure you dependencies file has
the correct spelling.  You might also try installing the
conda-env-pip package to see if provides the required
installer.
```
The combination of changing python 3.6 to 3.5 and also installing a pip package with the same environment file breaks the installer.",{},{}
