15409,IssuesEvent,2018-07-02 10:34:44+00:00,60273704,mozilla/DeepSpeech,399535,nh2,131524,mozilla,closed,16000Hz WAV file recorded by audacity is rejected,[],[],1,"From the README:

> Once everything is installed you can then use the deepspeech binary to do speech-to-text on short, approximately 5 second, audio files (currently only WAVE files with 16-bit, 16 kHz, mono are supported in the Python client)

So I created a 16kHz with Audacity on Ubuntu 16.04 using the format selection `WAV (Microsoft) signed 16-bit PCM`:

```
% file ~/tmp/test.wav 
/home/niklas/tmp/test.wav: RIFF (little-endian) data, WAVE audio, Microsoft PCM, 16 bit, mono 44100 Hz
```

`deepspeech` rejects it with:

```
% deepspeech models/output_graph.pb ~/tmp/test.wav models/alphabet.txt 
Loading model from file models/output_graph.pb
2018-07-02 12:16:47.702686: I tensorflow/core/platform/cpu_feature_guard.cc:137] Your CPU supports instructions that this TensorFlow binary was not compiled to use: AVX2 FMA
