15554,IssuesEvent,2017-01-24 05:36:54+00:00,69835022,cs50/python-cs50,788678,dmalan,788676,cs50,opened,test cs50.SQL,[],"[{'login': 'kzidane', 'id': 7230211, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/7230211?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/kzidane', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/kzidane/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",0,"Ideal to (re-)test SELECTs, INSERTs (with autoincrementing primary keys), UPDATEs, and DELETEs with:

* SQLite
* MySQL
* PostgreSQL

PostgreSQL, in particular, seems not to support [`lastrowid`](http://docs.sqlalchemy.org/en/latest/core/connections.html#sqlalchemy.engine.ResultProxy.lastrowid) (cf. http://stackoverflow.com/a/2189662), so I suspect this condition won't catch INSERTs in the same way:

```python
# if INSERT, return primary key value for a newly inserted row
elif result.lastrowid is not None:
    return result.lastrowid
```

Ergo the parenthetical comments:

```python
# if SELECT (or INSERT with RETURNING), return result set as list of dict objects
...
# if DELETE or UPDATE (or INSERT without RETURNING), return number of rows matched
```

Goal, then, is to test whether `execute` indeed behaves exactly as the comments and return values imply:

```python
# if SELECT (or INSERT with RETURNING), return result set as list of dict objects
if result.returns_rows:
    rows = result.fetchall()
    return [dict(row) for row in rows]

# if INSERT, return primary key value for a newly inserted row
elif result.lastrowid is not None:
    return result.lastrowid

# if DELETE or UPDATE (or INSERT without RETURNING), return number of rows matched
else:
    return result.rowcount
```

CC @glennholloway @brianyu28 ",{},{}
