15703,IssuesEvent,2018-03-15 03:17:20+00:00,90912724,mymarilyn/clickhouse-driver,5335295,Thordin,22597834,mymarilyn,closed,Dates are lower by 1,[],[],3,"date.fromtimestamp is supposed to take a local timestamp not a UTC one. I am in a timezone that is behind UTC, so all dates are 1 day behind.

```
>>> datetime.date.fromtimestamp(0)
datetime.date(1969, 12, 31)
```

To fix this you need to use datetime.datetime.utcfromtimestamp().date() instead.

https://github.com/mymarilyn/clickhouse-driver/blob/a3a26513d9533f389674c34c19ed7f8dd94b5289/src/columns/datecolumn.py#L18

`return datetime.datetime.utcfromtimestamp(value * self.offset).date()`",{},{}
15709,IssuesEvent,2017-06-14 22:03:45+00:00,552926,django-ckeditor/django-ckeditor,987055,karolyi,9961418,django-ckeditor,opened,"ckeditor/ckeditor_uploader/admin_base.css missing, hence browser will HTTP 500 in production mode",[],[],0,"hey,

I'm using `django-pipeline` which compiles all the static assets into their versioned files, and then uses a json file to find those files when serving live content. 

When Django is running in live mode, since `ckeditor/ckeditor_uploader/admin_base.css` is missing, the file browser view which uses this css, will result in a `HTTP 500`.

please either remove the file requirement from `ckeditor_uploader/templates/ckeditor/browse.html`, or put the file in place.

cheers,
László",{},{}
15710,IssuesEvent,2015-06-03 06:40:33+00:00,552926,django-ckeditor/django-ckeditor,12655600,cubiczx,9961418,django-ckeditor,opened,When order SortableStackedInline CKEditor iframe content disappears,[],[],0,"When order SortableStackedInline CKEditor iframe content disappears, this not occurs with other editors as django-suit-redactor.",{},{}
15711,IssuesEvent,2017-04-03 14:43:35+00:00,552926,django-ckeditor/django-ckeditor,218738,crucialfelix,9961418,django-ckeditor,opened,A way to set window.CKEDITOR_BASEPATH ?,[],[],0,"I cannot find anything in the docs or source code.

Due to some silliness between angular router and Django  I've needed to explicitly set the base href on my admin pages:

```html
 <base href=""/admin/nsmailings/openhousemailing/add/"">
```

Now CKEDITOR incorrectly finds the static files, thinking they must be relative to the base:

```
/admin/nsmailings/openhousemailing/add/config.js/change/ Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 404 (Not Found)

/admin/nsmailings/openhousemailing/add/skins/moono-lisa/editor.css/change/ Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 404 (Not Found)

/admin/nsmailings/openhousemailing/add/lang/en.js/change/ Failed to load resource: the server responded with a status of 404 (Not Found)
```

I now have to set the javascript variable by stuffing this in my admin change_form.html:

```html
<script>
  window.CKEDITOR_BASEPATH = '/static/ckeditor/ckeditor/';
</script>
```

TBH I'm not quite sure how django-ckeditor could easily offer some way to pass through django settings like this.  Maybe there isn't anything that you can do that is convoluted.



",{},{}
