15844,IssuesEvent,2016-03-02 23:52:22+00:00,7137821,cloudtools/troposphere,2269440,alonsodomin,3028687,cloudtools,opened,Add support for EMR Resources,[],[],0,"CloudFormation just recently added support for EMR resources:
https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/whats-new/2016/02/aws-cloudformation-adds-support-for-amazon-vpc-nat-gateway-amazon-ec2-container-registry-and-more/

It has happened this latest addition to CloudFormation was added in the moment that me and my colleagues were actually experimenting with it using CloudFormation CustomResources and Lambda Functions.

Adding pure ""native"" support sounds simpler though and we already have prototyped something extending Troposphere AWSObject & AWSProperty base objects. We are happy to PR it if no one else is working on it",{},{}
15857,IssuesEvent,2017-10-31 15:29:16+00:00,87362999,click-contrib/sphinx-click,1797906,jamesstidard,13245136,click-contrib,opened,Greater Import Error Context / Stack Trace,[],[],0,"python 3.4.6
sphinx-click 1.0.3
sphinx 1.5.3

Currently if there is an error when building the documentation any failures importing will be reported like this:

```bash
reading sources... [100%] pages/my_page                                                                                                                                                                                                
/path/to/pages/my_page.rst:1: ERROR: Failed to import ""cli"" from ""src.cli.__main__""
```
In my case this import was failing due to a silly syntax error I introduced somewhere in my source code.

It would be nice to have that stack trace of the syntax error pushed up to the command's output so it's easier to diagnose the cause of the failed import.

Thanks.",{},{}
