16402,IssuesEvent,2015-02-02 20:59:31+00:00,10247874,docker/docker-py,1494248,MrMMorris,5429470,docker,opened,Feature: Create Automated Builds with API,[],[],0,"This use case just occurred to me: developers are working away on their own branch and they want to put it onto a server. Currently, this would require manually creating a new automated build for that branch, waiting for it to build and then pushing the image to a server. 

It would be nice if you could create new automated builds through the API. Then I could just add a git update hook to run when a new branch is created and create a new build. Either that, or have a setting that says: ""Create automated build for all branches"" or something.

Thoughts?",{},{}
