16745,IssuesEvent,2017-11-16 22:09:24+00:00,30509483,clab/dynet,5590702,duyvuleo,2374376,clab,opened,possible bug of select_cols?,[],[],0,"Hi,

I've had a weird test result on select_cols, e.g., 

```
import dynet as dy

mod = dy.Model()

pv = mod.add_lookup_parameters((20, 5))

ix_batch = dy.lookup_batch(pv, [1, 2 ,3])
iy_batch = dy.lookup_batch(pv, [4, 5, 6])
ixy_batch = dy.concatenate_cols([ix_batch, iy_batch])
print ""ixy_batch.dim(): "" + ixy_batch.dim()

ixy_col = dy.select_cols(ixy_batch, [0])
print ""ixy_col.dim(): "" + str(ixy_col.dim()

ixy_row = dy.select_rows(ixy_batch, [0])
print ""ixy_row.dim(): "" +str(ixy_row.dim())
```

Results:
ixy_batch.dim(): ((5, 2), 3)
ixy_col.dim(): ((5, 1), **1**)
ixy_row.dim(): ((1, 2), 3)

ixy_col.dim() should retain the batch size, right? perhaps a bug in select_cols? 

Thanks!
",{},{}
