17042,IssuesEvent,2015-08-01 05:27:53+00:00,5888353,spotify/luigi,965782,jimjh,251374,spotify,opened,RangeBase executes tasks out of order,[],[],0,"See https://github.com/spotify/luigi/blob/master/luigi/tools/range.py

Inside `RangeBase`, we sort `missing_datetimes`, and we allow users to use `reverse` to reverse the ordering of the missing datetimes. However, these seem to be in vain, since the tasks from `requires()` are not guaranteed to be executed in the order they were returned.

```py
import luigi
import datetime


class Test(luigi.Task):

    dt = luigi.DateMinuteParameter()
    latest = datetime.datetime(2014, 05, 01)

    def run(self):
        print self.dt
        Test.latest = max(Test.latest, self.dt)

    def complete(self):
        return self.dt <= Test.latest

    @classmethod
    def bulk_complete(cls, *args, **kwargs):
        return []

if __name__ == '__main__':
    luigi.run()
```

```bash
python task.py RangeHourly --of Test --start 2015-05-01T00 --stop 2015-05-02T00 --local-scheduler 2> /dev/null
```

### Output

```
2015-05-01 06:00:00
2015-05-01 03:00:00
2015-05-01 00:00:00
2015-05-01 20:00:00
2015-05-01 08:00:00
2015-05-01 16:00:00
2015-05-01 04:00:00
2015-05-01 21:00:00
2015-05-01 22:00:00
2015-05-01 14:00:00
2015-05-01 11:00:00
2015-05-01 12:00:00
2015-05-01 19:00:00
2015-05-01 09:00:00
2015-05-01 15:00:00
2015-05-01 10:00:00
2015-05-01 13:00:00
2015-05-01 18:00:00
2015-05-01 23:00:00
2015-05-01 05:00:00
2015-05-01 17:00:00
2015-05-01 07:00:00
2015-05-01 02:00:00
2015-05-01 01:00:00
```",{},{}
