17106,IssuesEvent,2018-02-20 17:03:27+00:00,5888353,spotify/luigi,1052649,FxIII,251374,spotify,opened,race condition on lock :(,[],[],0,"I think there is a race condition on 
**luigi/lock.py"", line 93, in acquire_for**

```python
# Check if there is a pid file corresponding to this name
if not os.path.exists(pid_dir):
  os.mkdir(pid_dir)
```
between `if not [...]` and `mkdir` another process could have created the pid_dir resulting  in an unhandled OSError exception.

I think that ignore the exception if the folder exists will be enough, or perhaps just create the folder and say sorry if it was just there...
",{},{}
