17548,IssuesEvent,2018-04-20 09:09:20+00:00,103890505,ConsenSys/mythril,5194767,b-mueller,10818037,ConsenSys,closed,--init-db will hang around the 1000 contract mark,"[{'id': 695308627, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/ConsenSys/mythril/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'ee0701', 'default': True}]","[{'login': 'b-mueller', 'id': 5194767, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/5194767?v=4', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/b-mueller', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/b-mueller/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",1,"## Overview

Within the past few releases, the `--init-db` command will hang / fail to progress around the ~1000 unique contract mark.  

Expected behavior: Mythril will continue to scan and build the contract database to completion.
Actual Result: Mythril begins to slow before hanging, around ~1000 unique contracts.

## Remarks 

This only seems to happen when generating a new database / from scratch. It also seems to be a recent regression, possibly a deadlock with the recent addition of threading. I was able to build a database prior to the multiprocessing work.

Re-running `--init-db` with an already fully built database does not seem to reproduce this issue. 

I use a local, fully sync'd ETH node (geth 1.8.3).

## Repro

1. Delete any existitng mythril database, eg `rm -rf ~/.mythril/`
2. Run mythril and try to enumerate the database. `myth --init-db --rpc localhost:8545`
3. mythril should hang around the ~1000 unique contract mark. Probably coincidence, but it seems consistent.

Platform: Ubuntu 16.04 server, 8 cores, 8gb RAM + 8gb Swap
",{},{}
17549,IssuesEvent,2018-07-03 03:51:13+00:00,103890505,ConsenSys/mythril,22396913,TonyZhouCH,10818037,ConsenSys,opened,Mythril's results are't consistent,[],[],0,"**Describe the bug**
Guys, sorry to bother you again.
I'm not sure it is a bug. I use mythril to detect the vulnerability of one contract. However, I find out that the results reported by mythri are different.
I use json output format.Here is my result.
+ 1st time：Issues contain
    + Message call to external contract
    + Multiple Calls
    + Exception state
+ 2nd time: No issues
+ 3rd time: Issues contain
    + Message call to external contract
    + Exception state
    + Integer Overflow
It confuse me.How does it happen?
I uploaded the source code and result so you can inspect it.

 ",{},{}
