17617,IssuesEvent,2016-07-08 23:06:27+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,649860,SwartzCr,17889013,certbot,closed,certbot removes http->https rules corrupts ruleset,"[{'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/apache', 'name': 'apache', 'color': 'fbca04'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/bug', 'name': 'bug', 'color': 'fc2929'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/has%20pr', 'name': 'has pr', 'color': '0052cc'}, {'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/certbot/certbot/labels/security%20enhancements', 'name': 'security enhancements', 'color': 'ffb8f0'}]","[{'login': 'sagi', 'id': 6293471, 'avatar_url': 'https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/6293471?v=3', 'gravatar_id': '', 'url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi', 'html_url': 'https://github.com/sagi', 'followers_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/followers', 'following_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/following{/other_user}', 'gists_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/gists{/gist_id}', 'starred_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/starred{/owner}{/repo}', 'subscriptions_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/subscriptions', 'organizations_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/orgs', 'repos_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/repos', 'events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/events{/privacy}', 'received_events_url': 'https://api.github.com/users/sagi/received_events', 'type': 'User', 'site_admin': False}]",2,"certbot removes rewrite-rules which may result in endless forwarding rules. It should also remove the corresponding conditions because this corrupts the ruleset otherwise.

Here is my ruleset:

RewriteEngine On
RewriteCond %{HTTPS} !=on
RewriteRule .* https://%{SERVER_NAME}%{REQUEST_URI} [NE,R,L]
RewriteCond %{DOCUMENT_ROOT}/%{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteRule ^/(.*)$ balancer://unicornservers%{REQUEST_URI} [P,QSA,L]


certbot changes this to:

RewriteEngine On
RewriteCond %{HTTPS} !=on
#RewriteRule .* https://%{SERVER_NAME}%{REQUEST_URI} [NE,R,L]
RewriteCond %{DOCUMENT_ROOT}/%{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteRule ^/(.*)$ balancer://unicornservers%{REQUEST_URI} [P,QSA,L]

Now the RewriteCond in line 1 is applied to the last RewriteRule and changes thereby the conditions for this rule.",{},{}
