17908,IssuesEvent,2018-01-21 19:24:13+00:00,16865424,pimutils/vdirsyncer,837573,untitaker,17852924,pimutils,closed,store vcards by group,"[{'id': 344407071, 'url': 'https://api.github.com/repos/pimutils/vdirsyncer/labels/planning', 'name': 'planning', 'color': 'e6e6e6', 'default': False}]",[],8,"Hi everyone,

first, let me thank for your great work. I am currently using vdirsyncer for khal and khard, but also claws-mail (got it running thanks to the coments in #314). I am now quite happy with one exception: I would like to be able to use the vcard group property (either KIND=group as in the [vCard 4 RFC](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6350#section-6.1.4) or similarly with X-ADDRESSBOOKSERVER-KIND backported to vCard3, as used by e.g. Apple, fastmail, ...). In principle, these properties are in the vCards themselves, so grouping should be done in the client. However, as an intermediate solution for claws-mail, where vCard is not so well supported, I would like vdirsyncer to have the ability to use something like the ""singlefile"" type that stores the vCards not in one single file, but in one file per group instead. Then it would be relatively easy to set up claws-mail to respect these groups (automatic adding of new group would still not be possible, and support would of course be read-only, but at least the group information would be there).
Note that this kind of storage would have some degree of redundancy, as vCards are allowed to be part of more than one group.
I am willing to do the coding myself, but before I start hacking and initiate a pull request, I wanted to hear whether other users would be interested in this or whether the devs would oppose such a (admittedly not totally elegant) solution.
## <bountysource-plugin>

Want to back this issue? **[Post a bounty on it!](https://www.bountysource.com/issues/29808209-store-vcards-by-group?utm_campaign=plugin&utm_content=tracker%2F574345&utm_medium=issues&utm_source=github)** We accept bounties via [Bountysource](https://www.bountysource.com/?utm_campaign=plugin&utm_content=tracker%2F574345&utm_medium=issues&utm_source=github).
</bountysource-plugin>
