17932,IssuesEvent,2016-03-14 22:54:09+00:00,28201627,dropbox/nsot,12106450,dmar42,559357,dropbox,closed,API Support for closest parent network,[],[],5,"While shouldn't be the default, I would like to see an option for searching for the closest parent network. In my case, most users expect when searching for `10.250.0.1` to get the info for `10.250.0.0/24` or `10.250.0.0/16` and so on.

I have a couple workarounds in some apps which if given a `/32`, try for every length `range(32)` until ultimately saying sorry. Obviously this is quite slow if the closest result is a /8 or nonexistent altogether.

From an API perspective, I see this usecase similar to `/subnets` and `/supernets`: `GET /sites/1/networks/10.250.0.1/32/recurse`",{},{}
